    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-27T11:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-27T11:48:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/11–2251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-27T11:48:00-05:00"
                            >November 27, 1951—11:48 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 259. Do not understand reference <gloss
                        target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 312 to Fr proposal to divide Newsgathering
                    Convention into two Conventions.<note n="1" xml:id="d527fn1">In the Delegation’s
                        classified information summary for November 22, transmitted in <gloss
                            target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 312, November 22, mention was made that
                        the United Kingdom was “indifferent” to a “French proposal” to divide the
                        Newsgathering and Right of Corrections Convention into two conventions
                        (320/11–2251).</note> Has Fr abandoned proposal single Convention Eight
                    Correction in favor dividing Newsgathering text into two optional
                    conventions?</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> awaiting report high-level approach FrDel
                    suggested <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 64<note n="2" xml:id="d527fn2"
                        >Dated November 5, p. 811.</note> and concerned that <gloss
                        target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> may be forced accept two conventions
                    without any assurance support for newsgathering provisions. Even with such
                    assurance important divided convention be supported only last resort as means
                    preventing adoption original Fr proposal as suggested <gloss target="#t_Gadel2"
                        >Gadel</gloss> 183.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
